  <notes-results>
    <date>2026-06-26</date>
    <status>completed</status>
    <scope-note>Main session expanded scope beyond original POML (which deferred writers/reader to Phase 4 task 040) to match FR-12 acceptance criteria verbatim. All writer + reader updates landed in this task.</scope-note>

    <schema-change>
      Added `tenantId` field to `infrastructure/ai-search/spaarke-records-index.json` at
      position 2 (between `id` and `recordType`). Config: Edm.String, key=false,
      searchable=false, filterable=true, retrievable=true, sortable=true, facetable=true.
      Matches FR-12 acceptance exactly. No NFR-09 override comment needed (canonical policy).
    </schema-change>

    <writers-updated>
      <writer-1>
        File: src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/RecordMatching/SearchIndexDocument.cs
        Added TenantId property (SimpleField, JsonPropertyName="tenantId") at position 2.
      </writer-1>
      <writer-1-call-site>
        File: src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/RecordMatching/DataverseIndexSyncService.cs (TransformToDocument)
        Resolves tenantId from `_configuration["AzureAd:TenantId"]` and populates document.TenantId.
      </writer-1-call-site>
      <writer-2>
        File: src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/RecordSyncJob.cs (RecordSearchDocument class)
        Added TenantId property (JsonPropertyName="tenantId") at position 2.
      </writer-2>
      <writer-2-call-site>
        File: src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Jobs/RecordSyncJob.cs (SyncEntityAsync + MapToSearchDocument)
        Resolves tenantId once per entity batch from `_configuration["AzureAd:TenantId"]`,
        passes as new optional parameter to `MapToSearchDocument(record, entity, tenantId)`.
        Parameter is optional (default "") to preserve existing test call sites.
      </writer-2-call-site>
    </writers-updated>

    <reader-updated>
      <auth-filter>
        File: src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/RecordSearchAuthorizationFilter.cs
        Removed misleading "no tenantId field" workaround comment. Filter remains as
        authentication + audit gate. Replaced with note pointing to RecordSearchService
        where the OData filter is now applied.
      </auth-filter>
      <odata-filter>
        File: src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/RecordSearch/RecordSearchService.cs
        Updated BuildRecordFilter signature to accept tenantId. Added unconditional
        `tenantId eq '...'` predicate as filter position 0 (ALWAYS first, ALWAYS present
        per ADR-014 invariant — mirrors SearchFilterBuilder/SessionFilesCleanupJob pattern).
        Source of tenantId: existing `tenantIdForCache` resolution at top of SearchAsync
        (user 'tid' claim via IHttpContextAccessor; "system" fallback). Updated SelectFields
        to include "tenantId" so retrievable=true is honored end-to-end. Updated class-level
        remarks to remove "no tenantId field" wording and reference FR-12.
      </odata-filter>
    </reader-updated>

    <judgment-call name="tenant-source">
      Background services (DataverseIndexSyncService + RecordSyncJob) have NO user context.
      Per existing pattern in Email/Workers-Office/Communication services, the canonical
      tenant source for system-context services is `_configuration["AzureAd:TenantId"]`
      (the Azure AD tenant the BFF App Service is bound to — single-tenant per Dataverse
      environment by design). Reader path uses the user's 'tid' claim, which is correct
      for user-context search.
    </judgment-call>

    <judgment-call name="reader-filter-placement">
      User prompt said "update RecordSearchAuthorizationFilter.cs:43 to apply tenantId eq filter".
      Structurally, that endpoint filter cannot inject OData filters — it runs BEFORE the
      SearchOptions are constructed in RecordSearchService.BuildRecordFilter. The actual
      OData filter MUST live in RecordSearchService. Resolved by: removing the misleading
      comment in the auth filter (the workaround it claimed no longer applies) AND adding
      the `tenantId eq '...'` predicate to BuildRecordFilter where it belongs. Both sides
      of the user's instruction are addressed.
    </judgment-call>

    <judgment-call name="odata-syntax">
      Followed existing Spaarke pattern: `tenantId eq '{EscapeODataValue(tenantId)}'`
      (single-quote escaping via doubling, ADR-014 invariant). Mirrors
      SearchFilterBuilder.cs:71 + SessionFilesCleanupJob.cs:386 + EmbeddingMigrationService.cs:309.
    </judgment-call>

    <build-verification>
      Command: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`
      Result: Build succeeded — 0 Warning(s), 0 Error(s). Time elapsed 2.39s.
